{"id": "08ee5931100c65c94a20336a5c91589aef2a3d82c4f5379a870f763611ddb3f5", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:0", "text": "PxrAttribute allows the user to read attributes attached to (stored) on a node. Such an example would be to add a color attribute to a set of objects to be read by a material later. In this way, a material can change its result based on the object being rendered instead of a different material. Below there are color attributes attached to the sphere's of the shader ball. A single"}
{"id": "c94cdae36aaf9c8c015d0577e228c8c9e4590a382cf9ff02725718cbfc7da7c1", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:2", "text": "material renders with a different diffuse color as specific by each shape's defined attribute. Examples on usage are below."}
{"id": "4be21ca368d507bd0e9d58dd5bd6dae0955940b25ca1385d58b05792177c398a", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:3", "text": "There may be a performance penalty for using this node in many places in your scene. Efficiency is key to avoid too many evaluations of user attributes if not necessary."}
{"id": "0b64682bead3a63aff51f9d8e6ca1fe2d3a667318b56de644863d84e8973f896", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:5", "text": "Variable name"}
{"id": "2712910b5cfd83e086e353a5da633f37f67e9d1ab3650ae86d9553cd85b269c2", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:6", "text": "This field takes a string that identifies the attribute.  The string should include the namespace for the attribute and the attribute name separated by a colon.  For example, trace:maxdiffusedepth or user:Ball."}
{"id": "7ca630531aa9347d9adc5a371ccb5f5a249f644a915a4449f515f844ae5246b2", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:7", "text": "Variable Type"}
{"id": "c9b1e693e743d971bcb7d2c3409b7c7269b203471faac61b24dbdf4fdb8cb75a", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:8", "text": "This specifies the type of variable to read and must match what was specified above on the other nodes."}
{"id": "2876814bd73accf51719d41f10f51e597dd474da7099427ed609ca5ee726fbb5", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:9", "text": "Integer"}
{"id": "1a693c00c40cc749294b6c88a58f62250fa3fba10d6e406567ce2bae2e572661", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:10", "text": "Float"}
{"id": "6772a8f0bf6eaa4474f1cb3dbde9a33c1f96a95041131f87f7ae87c4ff7e9ddb", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:11", "text": "Float 2"}
{"id": "2fc0c524431a923617b003031d19d1e02e729210afacbe3ee02337a43422634a", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:13", "text": "Point"}
{"id": "a56ad3f2440820608303a0d4a84b1f1858660ead830b8e7df8e8d0b5a7eed13a", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:14", "text": "Vector"}
{"id": "a7248eeb45eb1ce247f81693283e22e8b39e8a50890cecd22d02e75025547d90", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:15", "text": "Normal"}
{"id": "983667653c2e83329d15396ce353994808b176c3ae62afc21e9081b6e87251f3", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:16", "text": "Default Float"}
{"id": "fb00f6a9ecbd33e9ce7a0f4f9972acc3f24c569e57b0a8b626fa82231847d86a", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:17", "text": "If there is an error when retrieving an attribute of type float, this is the value that will be used."}
{"id": "9ef7fc32310bf163549d74a478dbe4d066dbffd5cc26a14980d9b4134dc3e528", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:18", "text": "Verbosity"}
{"id": "3b2fd38409d7760bb567231157021fccdff827faea12939aff88e73b9977f969", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:19", "text": "Diagnostic output levels for scene debugging"}
{"id": "ddbcf06726488a43af36838754808ac5041b05ab6434735615979d820725b56f", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:20", "text": "Silent"}
{"id": "0e04cd10f9afd7e546e176b34b56a243d8c741198aa0bfee27d7661a370dc043", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:21", "text": "Warnings"}
{"id": "170322a32f3c35b2c61576a5553d352d7b3c8ae7086dab78f15fc891a28c067c", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:22", "text": "Info"}
{"id": "8b76e2df9050f924b018cff8809cbc580f39a71664984ae54adf99defe9eaa2e", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:23", "text": "Output Parameters"}
{"id": "20cee54d3870761a41a354946a213694c0612e819dc7d1e21f529a8e727fb539", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:24", "text": "resultF"}
{"id": "0e32073f25e1a2fcfb829561895b54b3a3bf98e5feccbe294bc71b470b24d0e3", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:25", "text": "A float result."}
{"id": "d76cd2ea3537dbac1a9b90ba977fe5ad654d6f7f3c36b060963224d8b5611f99", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:26", "text": "resultRGB"}
{"id": "11e1b24f86e144bbc59b2b9fb8d6d9d80b06582a73ac5173cfe1c6ae5522bf82", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:27", "text": "The color result."}
{"id": "eda240bae926d0cc7c18251b3f4ad5b99fc983f8eae4aea7cb3df39fdf71566d", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:29", "text": "DCC applications may use a different mechanism for applying a user attribute. Below are two examples for applying a color user attribute named \"Ball\" to a shape:"}
{"id": "65fd8403b2e164a82ff3d434931d77de4616db9b58fbe314eab5b9aa3a32621c", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:30", "text": "Maya:"}
{"id": "fce56d686e8f9f5e0a0e33f8be1e9c7c76e568b1b08ea4b36027fe0209410465", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:31", "text": "Add a user attribute from the Maya Attribute editor transform node, Name: Ball Type: color Color: Light Pink. The resulting export is below, note that we assume a User attribute from the Maya Editor automatically and does not need to be specified."}
{"id": "23d4a9d3fad63b1018d484cf2bece4647fe4187fbe8a0fc5f6b1e3c9b9967e2a", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:32", "text": "Katana:"}
{"id": "d0d6df61bfc8ef2cce88fc5e0a591c2e51c5db40000eff04015e2d3833139c95", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:33", "text": "The below is an OpScript example of the same attribute in Katana"}
{"id": "1f65179b4dad3176b194b87b65af239fbf4c0cad7dad742b4a2ffca8718f71eb", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:34", "text": "gb = GroupBuilder()"}
{"id": "0d55a3c2567d84761c9c990cc9327ce5eaadba82542e8ab3048e0d7e4034f8cb", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:35", "text": "gb:set(\"value\", FloatAttribute({1.0, 0.2, 0.65}, 3))"}
{"id": "67d4ffeb6dd2f72b48cf76d17d45386c6938454dc7ac37809433eea2260407e7", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:36", "text": "gb:set(\"type\", StringAttribute(\"color\"))"}
{"id": "da88b57bdd38cc16601570a8b65ccb2b16039334385440b6ce401367758322c5", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:37", "text": "Interface.SetAttr(\"prmanStatements.attributes.user.Ball\", gb:build())"}
{"id": "a5f9b4599f3c650465465ccfbc5d7227c6eb64cd85b6bc99f876a3c9f10bab88", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:38", "text": "Houdini:"}
{"id": "2f9d0b1505ab5f2f1eeeb452ddcaaacbd1efb74db2c28db6e3783b7b808421f9", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:40", "text": "Using PxrMatteID"}
{"id": "b167b209fe1409f9150908ed83c01f174298e3fbfca4324e44d1b4969cb07257", "item_id": "0a3688c0ed:41", "text": "as an example of how to add user attribute in Houdini."}
